<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Islington on 05-31-2001 01:45 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I did the Wurm camps several times with Islington and saw about 4 or 5 copies of the spell drop.  I personally gave 2 away to guildmates.  However hindsight being 20/20, I got screwed in the end.  The copies I saw drop were in the first two weeks of Velious going live when each Guardian was pretty much guaranteed to drop up to three spells.  I went back to the Wurm camp after the infamous “spell drop nerf” and got so frustrated that I vowed to never do it again. Also it just so happens that shortly after I gave the copies away to guildmates, I did so to better the guild and help us out.  Well in both cases the guildmates left the guild shortly after looking for “raiding” style guilds…

As soon as Quistil hit 39 I sold off a lot of junk (including my coveted Ghoulbane…  Sigh…) and managed to raise 2.5k (said Ghoulbane just isn’t worth what it once was).  I started to auction in every single zone I was in for Celestial Healing and never got a single tell for a week.  Kept checking with my guild but no joy there either.  I posted on the trades section of my servers board and finally found a seller.  I was hoping to pay 1k or less for the spell.  I was willing to blow the whole 2.5k on it.  He wanted 2k for it but I managed to talk him down to 1.5k.  So I got it for far less than I was willing to buy it for but more than I wanted to.

Overall I’m happy though.  It sits in my backpack with my other 44 spells just waiting for the day I can scribe it  :)


------------------
Quistil Angelwatch
Cleric of 40 Seasons in the service to the Great Mother Tunare
Islington Angelwatch (Semi Retired)
Paladin of 53 Seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr
Phoenix Crusaders</TEXTAREA>
